Package com.iontrading.mkv

Class MkvObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.iontrading.mkv.MkvObject
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MkvChain, MkvFunction, MkvPattern, MkvRecord, MkvRecordset, MkvType, MkvView
    @Keep
@KeepPublicClassMemberNames
public class MkvObject
extends Object
    The MkvObject class wraps a ION Bus Publish in a Java Object.

    This is the base class for all others objects that are managed by this API. Moreover it provides and stores informations common to all objects.
    The creation of remote MkvObject (that is objects incoming from a remote component) is notified via MkvPublishListener listener invocations.

    See Also:
    MkvChain, MkvFunction, MkvRecord, MkvType, MkvView, MkvPublishListener, MkvPublishManager

      • publish

        public void publish()
             throws MkvObjectNotLocalException,
                    MkvException
        Publish this MkvObject.

        The ION Object represented by this MkvObject will be made available to the other components of the ION Platform this application is connected to. Furthermore this MkvObject is registered into this application Data Dictionary, this means it can be obtained through the find methods of MkvPublishManager.

        Throws:
        MkvObjectNotLocalException - if the object was not locally created.
        MkvException - if the object cannot be published.
        See Also:
        MkvPublishManager

      • unpublish

        public void unpublish()
               throws MkvObjectNotLocalException,
                      MkvObjectNotAvailableException
        Unpublish this MkvObject.

        The ION Object represented by this MkvObject will become unavailable to the other components connected with this application. Furthermore this MkvObject is removed from this application Data Dictionary, this means it cannot be longer obtained through the find methods of MkvPublishManager.

        Throws:
        MkvObjectNotLocalException - if the object was not locally created.
        MkvObjectNotAvailableException - if the object was not published.
        See Also:
        MkvPublishManager
